// Launch System optimized logical schema for dbdiagram.io
// Target: PostgreSQL 16+

Project launch_system_optimized {
  database_type: 'PostgreSQL'
  Note: '''
  Hardened logical design derived from the SRS and schema review. UUIDs are application/generated UUIDv7 where approved; timestamptz values are UTC instants; quantities and money use numeric(20,4). All FK deletes default to RESTRICT/NO ACTION in executable DDL.

  DBML limitations: CHECK constraints, partial UNIQUE indexes, UNIQUE NULLS NOT DISTINCT, EXCLUDE constraints, generated expressions, deferred constraint triggers, RLS, append-only privileges, and hash-chain procedures are recorded in table/column notes and must be implemented in PostgreSQL migrations. Notes are requirements, not claims that dbdiagram enforces them.

  Open decisions: OP-01 FGPN length/format; OP-02..04 role scope; OP-05 backward PO transitions; OP-06 multi-PO tie-breaking; OP-07 accepted confirmation evidence; OP-08 delivery methods; OP-09 coefficient policy; OP-10 receipt validator/SLA; OP-11 invoice applicability; OP-12 draft retention; OP-13 delivery-code TTL; DS-14 stock ownership scope; PI-15 stable PO/item identity. Provisional enum values must be seed-reviewed before production.

  Core facts never reference reference_list_items. That generic catalog is restricted to non-authoritative extensions. Physical stock uses stock pools and locations; simulations snapshot inputs; PO/BOM/status/production/inventory/delivery/price/audit facts are immutable and corrected by new events or reversals.

  Omitted projections/views (derive from immutable facts, never edit as source data): v_operational_dashboard, v_po_item_balance, v_simulation_shortfalls, v_launch_readiness, v_inventory_balance, v_stock_summary, v_actual_sales, v_period_revenue, v_forecast_vs_actual, v_project_lifecycle_audit, v_actionable_dashboard. Finance views include v_actual_sales, v_period_revenue, and v_forecast_vs_actual; transport cost is counted once per shipment.
  '''
}

